Isolation and segmentation in Azure VNets are achieved using subnets, Network Security Groups (NSGs), and routing rules.

Isolation ensures that resources are protected from unauthorized access, while segmentation divides the network into logical sections.

For example, a database can be placed in a private subnet with no internet access.

A real-life use case is a financial system where sensitive data is isolated from public-facing services.

Another example is separating development, testing, and production environments to avoid interference.

Isolation and segmentation improve security, performance, and manageability.
